OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774505051
OL,3,CParty leaders start campaign push
OL,4,Cahead of Holyrood vote
OL,6,FSpeaking ahead of the campaign launch,
OL,7,Fthe SNP leader said: "Be in no doubt,
OL,8,Fwithout an SNP majority there is
OL,9,Falways the potential for a grubby,
OL,10,Fbackroom deal between Labour and
OL,11,FReform."
OL,13,FMr Sarwar, however, insisted the
OL,14,Fupcoming election was "the first
OL,15,Fopportunity in a generation to change
OL,16,Fthe government in Scotland", with the
OL,17,FScottish Labour leader telling voters:
OL,18,F"It is not one we can afford to miss.
OL,26,@oD@VOUsD@HO]vD@WOUxD@[O]zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774505051
OL,3,CParty leaders start campaign push
OL,4,Cahead of Holyrood vote
OL,6,F"After 20 years of SNP government,
OL,7,FScotland needs change, and this is the
OL,8,Fonly party that can deliver it.
OL,10,F"Scotland's choice is a simple one ` a
OL,11,Fthird decade of SNP Government with
OL,12,FJohn Swinney as first minister, or a
OL,13,FScottish Labour government with me as
OL,14,Ffirst minister."
OL,16,FThe Scottish Tory leader, meanwhile,
OL,17,Furged voters to back his party to
OL,18,F"stop Swinney and his push to break up
OL,19,Fthe United Kingdom".
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUvD@PO]zD@AOU{D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
