OL,3,CParty leaders start campaign push
OL,4,Cahead of Holyrood vote
OL,6,FMr Findlay said polling had already
OL,7,Findicated the SNP is on the brink of a
OL,8,Fmajority ` branding this a "nightmare
OL,9,Fprospect".
OL,11,FWhile he claimed Mr Swinney was
OL,12,F"already boasting about winning a
OL,13,Fmajority", the Conservative leader
OL,14,Fstated: "If Scots get behind the
OL,15,FScottish Conservatives, we can stop
OL,16,FSwinney and his push to break up the
OL,17,FUnited Kingdom."
OL,26,@pD@\OUqD@IO]tD@AOUuD@IO]vD@IOUyD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
