CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774505051
OL,3,CParty leaders start campaign push
OL,4,Cahead of Holyrood vote
OL,6,FScottish Green co-leader Gillian
OL,7,FMackay claimed that Scotland was being
OL,8,F"held back by a tired, broken and
OL,9,Fincompetent Labour government, and an
OL,10,FSNP who won't take the action that is
OL,11,Fneeded".
OL,13,FShe said: "Over the weeks ahead we
OL,14,Fwill be speaking to communities all
OL,15,Facross Scotland, listening to them and
OL,16,Fsharing our plans for a fairer,
OL,17,Fgreener and better future."
OL,26,@pD@AOUsD@GO]uD@KOUyD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
